s, arguing that the goal of early modern artists was not the creation of a naturalistically unified stage constructed for a single, privileged viewer, but rather a complex multimedia experience addressing a diverse set of viewers. In stressing the wider scenographic possibilities of the sixteenth-century stage, the book focuses on how space created various modes of audience engagement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aItalian dramayTo 1700xHistory and criticism. 0aTheater audiences. 0aTheaterzItalyxHistoryy16th century. 0aTheatersxStage-setting and sceneryzItalyxHistoryy16th century. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh  aTheatre architecture.  acity views.  adrama.  aearly modern.  alinear perspective.  ascenography.  asixteenth century.  atheatre design.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2019z9783110605747oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487518981423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487518981.jpg  a978-3-11-061001-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  